<paragraph blockId="0.[151,524,1912,1974]" box="[151,263,1948,1974]" pageId="0" pageNumber="583">
<figureCitation box="[151,258,1948,1974]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 2" captionStart-1="FIGURE 3" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1280,1305]" captionStartId-1="2.[151,250,1820,1845]" captionTargetBox-0="[164,1423,196,1240]" captionTargetBox-1="[153,1433,1339,1779]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[164,1423,196,1240]" captionTargetId-1="figure@2.[151,1436,1339,1779]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="2" captionText-0="FIGURE 2. Suwallia jihuae, sp. nov., holotype, male habitus. A. dorsal view; B. ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." captionText-1="FIGURE 3. Suwallia jihuae, sp. nov., holotype, male terminalia. A. dorsal view; B. caudal view; C. drawings of caudal view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/2702245/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/2702247/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="583">Figs. 2–3</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,2019,2046]" box="[151,1437,2019,2046]" pageId="0" pageNumber="583">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,319,2019,2046]" pageId="0" pageNumber="583">Adult habitus</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[337,410,2019,2046]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1280,1305]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,196,1240]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1423,196,1240]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Suwallia jihuae, sp. nov., holotype, male habitus. A. dorsal view; B. ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2702245/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="583">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Triocellate. Body generally pale, with brown patterns. Head with a brown oval stigma
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,153,990]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">covering the ocelli and the anterior of head. Compound eyes dark, ocelli with dark margins. Antenna brown, with at least 16 segments. Pronotum rugose and dark brown; meso- and metanota with dark U-shaped marks. Wings hyaline, fringed with short hairs; veins brown; Rs of forewing forked; anal field of hindwing small and folded with three veins. Femur pale, tibia and tarsus dark brown. Tergum 1 to anterior of tergum 9 with a longitudinal median stripe. Cercus seven-segmented, covered with long bristles.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,153,990]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,329,355]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[275,383,329,355]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 2" captionStart-1="FIGURE 3" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1280,1305]" captionStartId-1="2.[151,250,1820,1845]" captionTargetBox-0="[164,1423,196,1240]" captionTargetBox-1="[153,1433,1339,1779]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[164,1423,196,1240]" captionTargetId-1="figure@2.[151,1436,1339,1779]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="2" captionText-0="FIGURE 2. Suwallia jihuae, sp. nov., holotype, male habitus. A. dorsal view; B. ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." captionText-1="FIGURE 3. Suwallia jihuae, sp. nov., holotype, male terminalia. A. dorsal view; B. caudal view; C. drawings of caudal view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/2702245/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/2702247/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Figs. 2–3</figureCitation>
). Body length ca. 
<quantity box="[584,672,328,355]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
; forewings length ca. 
<quantity box="[916,1003,328,355]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
, hindwings length ca. 
<quantity box="[1252,1341,328,355]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
. Tergum 10 divided, median portion with an invaginated dark sclerite, shape of the sclerite resembling the letter “H” from caudal view. Hemitergal processes strongly sclerotized, finger-shaped and curved forward. Epiproct reduced to two small membranous lobes. Posterior of sternum 9 extended backwards, forming an expanded subgenital plate. Aedeagus not everted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,153,990]" box="[199,418,505,531]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,505,531]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
